{
  "stem": "6130.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "So my brother, Imre, whom I adored, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] risking his life again, jumped the fence during the night and went to a family, gentile family, who lived not too far from us-- very well-to-do people-- and begged for a little milk for my father.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "My mother happened to friendly with the wife of that family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And they wouldn't give it to him-- to him, because they knew if he would be caught and tortured, who gave the milk, they would get into trouble.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "So he-- he came back empty-handed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And it was such a tragedy, because he really risked his life, but he-- it was in the middle of the night, dark.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "So he jumped the fence.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "He came back.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And he went back the same way, on the train, in the toilet.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Then I don't know, how we let him know again that my-- my father died.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "That the only way-- the only time they let us out of the ghetto to go to the cemetery.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] There were two Christian women kneeling at the empty grave there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "One was a laundress who did my mother's laundry.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Came to the house and did the laundry, I don't know, maybe 30 years, 40 years.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "She was just-- she was just like a member of the family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "That's how she made her living.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And there was another one who lived across the street, but because it became the ghetto, she had to go out.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And she was a very poor woman, and my father many times gave her bread-- don't pay for it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And she was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "Those were the two people.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
